OCCs - Occupational Character Classes
The following Occupational Character Classes are available on RiftsMUD.
OCC-eligible races may choose one during character creation.
Type: help <occ name>  for details on any specific OCC.

GENERALIST
  Vagabond          - Adaptable wanderer and survivor, most skill picks
  City Rat          - Urban specialist, criminal skills and city connections
  Wilderness Scout  - Tracker, hunter, and outdoor survivalist
  Rogue Scholar     - Self-taught intellectual preserving pre-Rifts knowledge
  Merc Soldier      - Professional mercenary, flexible and reliable
  Tribal Warrior    - Wilderness fighter trained in native traditions

COMBAT / MERCENARY
  Headhunter        - Elite mercenary soldier for hire, heavy combat skills
  Bounty Hunter     - Pursuer of criminals, combining detection and combat
  Special Forces    - Elite mercenary special operations, demolitions expert
  Master Assassin   - Professional killer, stealth and precision
  Glitter Boy Pilot - Operator of the legendary pre-Rifts Glitter Boy armour
  Ninja Juicer      - Drug-enhanced warrior with martial arts training
  Juicer            - Combat stimulant-enhanced superhuman, shortened lifespan
  Hyperion Juicer   - Next-generation Juicer with superior enhancements
  Delphi Juicer     - Psychic-enhanced Juicer variant, limited clairvoyance
  Maxi-Man          - Nano-augmented near-superhuman soldier

COALITION STATES
  CS Grunt          - Standard Coalition infantry, Dead Boy armour
  CS Ranger         - Elite Coalition scout, wilderness operations
  CS Dead Boy       - Elite Coalition infantry, superior training and gear
  CS Military Spec  - Elite Coalition all-around specialist
  CS SAMAS Pilot    - Pilot of SAMAS flying power armour
  CS Tech Officer   - Coalition technical and engineering officer
  ISS Peacekeeper   - Coalition internal security, law enforcement
  ISS Specter       - Covert ISS operative, infiltration and elimination
  NTSET Protector   - Supernatural threat specialist, anti-demon unit

TECHNICAL / MEDICAL
  Robot Pilot       - Giant robot and power armour specialist
  Operator          - Technical genius, repairs and builds anything
  Rogue Scientist   - Independent scientist, pre-Rifts ruins explorer
  Cyber-Doc         - Cybernetics and bionics surgeon
  Body Fixer        - Field medic and surgeon
  Techno-Wizard     - Magic-tech hybrid, PPE-powered devices

STEALTH / CRIMINAL
  Bounty Hunter     - see above
  City Rat          - see above
  Professional Thief - Expert bypass and theft specialist
  Forger            - False identity and document specialist
  Freelance Spy     - Independent intelligence operative
  Smuggler          - Contraband runner and trader
  Master Assassin   - see above

KNIGHTS
  Cyber-Knight      - Psionic noble warrior with psi-sword, protects innocent
  Knight (Europe)   - Chivalric warrior of post-Rifts Europe
  Royal Knight      - Noble-appointed knight with political authority

REGIONAL
  Pirate (S.A.)     - South American coastal pirate and raider
  Sailor (S.A.)     - South American mariner and navigator

MAGIC USERS  (limited availability: requires high ME and/or IQ)
  Ley Line Walker   - Sorcerer attuned to ley lines, spells and rifting
  Ley Line Rifter   - Advanced rifter mage, dimensional travel specialist
  Shifter           - Summoner who opens Rifts, deals with supernatural beings
  Mystic            - Rare dual magic-user and psychic
  Shaman            - Tribal spirit mage and healer
  Techno-Wizard     - see above
  Tattooed Man      - PPE-powered magical tattoo warrior
  Air Warlock       - Elemental mage of air and lightning
  Gifted Gypsy      - Minor magic, fortune-telling, and herbalism

PSYCHIC / SPECIAL
  Crazy             - M.O.M. drug-psychic warrior, powerful but unstable
  Delphi Juicer     - see above
  Nega-Psychic      - Suppresses psychic and magical energies
  Borg              - Full conversion cyborg, mechanical body

Type: pick occ <name>   at character creation to choose your OCC.
